      "writtenOn": "2021-02-17T22:13:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Good question. In ynev the bottleneck is almost entirely sending data to the GPU. When I do a blanket enable of dynamic attribs there, the time goes from:\n\n5.87 -\u003e 7.24ms\n\nSo 1.25x the time for 1.3x the data. In light of that I would vote to keep the dynamic attrib flags for now. Lots of SVGs have long, complicated strokes that don\u0027t need dynamic attribs.\n\nOf course another option would be to pack the dynamic state into a texel buffer, where each instance just gets a single extra index for the fetch. But then that\u0027s potentially a lot of fetching when we want to add matrices if there isn\u0027t a flag to control the matrix type.",
      "parentUuid": "d7244b98_ad90a159",
      "revId": "803194b63bc2296fa8389d1ed5d6eef321182c74",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
